Sentencas: The purpose of this research was to obtain porous, high-quality cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells in both planar and tubular shapes.
Titulo: The Electrophoretic Deposition of Lanthanum Manganite Powders for a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell in Planar and Tubular Configurations

Sentencas: To accomplish this, cathodic electrophoretic deposition of the LaMnO3 powder (synthesized by the modified sol-gel method proposed by Pechini) was performed.
Titulo: The Electrophoretic Deposition of Lanthanum Manganite Powders for a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell in Planar and Tubular Configurations

Sentencas: The optimal sintering temperatures were 1200 degrees C and 1300 degrees C for the tubular and planar configurations, respectively.
Titulo: The Electrophoretic Deposition of Lanthanum Manganite Powders for a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell in Planar and Tubular Configurations

Sentencas: Single-phase deposits with about 40% porosity were obtained in both configurations.
Titulo: The Electrophoretic Deposition of Lanthanum Manganite Powders for a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell in Planar and Tubular Configurations

Sentencas: The cathode quality was confirmed by depositing an electrolyte layer of YSZ.
Titulo: The Electrophoretic Deposition of Lanthanum Manganite Powders for a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell in Planar and Tubular Configurations

Sentencas: After the cosintering of both layers, an extremely dense electrolyte layer was obtained, and the cathode layer retained its high porosity.
Titulo: The Electrophoretic Deposition of Lanthanum Manganite Powders for a Cathode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cell in Planar and Tubular Configurations
